Press Releases


VSE Corp Wins $37M USMC AAV Equipment Support Task Order


 Download as PDF

September 16, 2015


VSE to expand technical, maintenance and test support for the U.S.
      Marine Corps

    ALEXANDRIA, Va.--
      VSE Corporation (NASDAQ: VSEC) was recently awarded a Firm Fixed Price
      (FFP) task order under its SeaPort-e contract vehicle to support the
      U.S. Marine Corps Systems Command in Quantico, VA. This task order has a
      period of performance that includes a six-month base period and four
      one-year options with a total value of $37M. This award represents an
      increase in contract value, scope, and capabilities to work currently
      performed by VSE.
    

      Under this task order VSE will provide program management, engineering
      technical support, maintenance services, test and evaluation, logistics
      support, and vehicle and equipment storage for the USMC Product Manager
      Assault Amphibious Vehicles (PdM AAV) for the Equipment Maintenance Test
      Support (EMTS) Program. Throughout the period of performance, VSE will
      support the Product Manager (PdM) for the AAV test vehicles located at
      our AAV Maintenance Facility at Green Road, Ruther Glen, VA and multiple
      CONUS and OCONUS locations. Maintaining and testing the PdM AAV vehicles
      is the first step in moderizing the AAV Family of Vehicles (FOV) since
      the Marine Corps has extended the service life of the AAV to 2035.
    

      “For nearly two decades, we have provided comprehensive maintenance
      support for the USMC amphibious assault vehicles,” said Federal Services
      Group President J.R. Brown. “Our program manager, maintenance supervisor
      and mechanics, engineers, vehicle operators and field service
      technicians bring expertise, experience, and a level of detailed
      knowledge that will continue to keep these vehicles in the highest state
      of operational readiness for testing and demonstrations throughout their
      service life. Our number one goal is to ensure that our nation’s first
      line of defense is fully supported to accomplish their mission.”
    

About VSE


      Established in 1959, VSE is a diversified logistics and services company
      with experience in solving issues of global significance with integrity,
      agility, and value. VSE is dedicated to making our federal and
      commercial clients successful by delivering innovative solutions for
      vehicle, ship, and aircraft sustainment, supply chain management,
      platform modernization, mission enhancement, program management, energy,
      IT, and consulting services. For additional information regarding VSE
      services and products, please see the Company's web site at www.vsecorp.com
      or contact Christine Kaineg, VSE Investor Relations, at (703) 329-3263.
    





View source version on businesswire.com: http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20150916006566/en/

      VSE News ContactChristine Kaineg, 703-329-3263.
    


Source: VSE Corporation

Released September 16, 2015













  





 



